FBIS4-35271 "drnes104_n_94006" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 30 May 1994 LEBANON Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping Nasrallah Calls For End to Talks NC3005060194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0430 GMT 30 May 94 NC3005060194 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Hizballah Secretary General Hasan Nasrallah has called on the Lebanese Government to withdraw from the peace talks in response to Israel's abduction of Mustafa al-Dirani. He affirmed that civilian peace is in the interest of the resistance, coexistence, and building a state to which all Lebanese aspire. Al-Dirani's family yesterday appealed to the International Committee of the Red Cross [ICRC] to act quickly in providing medical assistance to him. In a memorandum submitted to the ICRC, al-Dirani's family held Israel responsible for the deterioration of his health and for preventing the Red Cross from visiting him.
